<!--
Author: mobilemutex
Date: 2026-01-15
Description: SEGGER J-Link device description file for the NXP MPC5674F microcontroller.

To use this file:
1. Place it in the appropriate JLinkDevices folder for your operating system:
   - Windows: C:\Users\<USER>\AppData\Roaming\SEGGER\JLinkDevices\NXP\MPC5674F\MPC5674F.xml
   - Linux:   $HOME/.config/SEGGER/JLinkDevices/NXP/MPC5674F/MPC5674F.xml
   - macOS:   $HOME/Library/Application Support/SEGGER/JLinkDevices/NXP/MPC5674F/MPC5674F.xml
2. Create the necessary subdirectories (e.g., NXP/MPC5674F) if they don't exist.

IMPORTANT NOTE ON FLASH PROGRAMMING:
J-Link does not have built-in flash programming support for the MPC56xx family.
This XML file will enable J-Link to recognize the MPC5674F for debugging purposes only.
To program the flash, you will need a separate flash loader file.
-->
<DataBase>
  <Device>
    <ChipInfo Vendor="NXP" Name="MPC5674F" Core="JLINK_CORE_POWER_PC" WorkRAMAddr="0x40008000" WorkRAMSize="0x00038000"/>
    <!--
      The FlashBankInfo section is commented out because a specific flash loader is required.
      To enable flash programming, you must:
      1. Obtain or create a compatible flash loader ELF file (e.g., MPC5674F.elf).
      2. Place the ELF file in the same directory as this XML file.
      3. Uncomment the FlashBankInfo section below.

    <FlashBankInfo Name="Flash" BaseAddr="0x00000000" AlwaysPresent="1">
      <LoaderInfo Name="Default" MaxSize="0x00400000" Loader="MPC5674F.elf" LoaderType="FLASH_ALGO_TYPE_OPEN" />
    </FlashBankInfo>
    -->
  </Device>
</DataBase>
